celDataFormat\":true,\"legend\":\"\",\"mergeCells\":{},\"printData\":[[\"Component \",\"Final conc.\",\"1Rxn (uL)\"],[\"H2O\",\"\",\"Up to 25ul\"],[\"T4 DNA ligase buffer\",\"1X\",\"2.5\"],[\"T4 DNA ligase (2,000U/ul)\",\"\",\"0.5\"],[\"Plasmid  (100ng/ul)\",\"2.5ng\",\"2.5\"],[\"SapI (10U/ul)\",\"20U\",\"2\"],[\"Insert (ul)\",\"1:2 mol ratio\",\"1.09\"],[\"Total\",\"\",\"25\"]],\"rowHeights\":[23,23,23,23,23,23,23,23]}},\"1\":{\"type\":\"tables\",\"mutability\":\"MUTABLE\",\"data\":{\"cellsMeta\":{\"0_0\":\"\",\"0_1\":\"\",\"0_2\":\"\",\"0_3\":\"\",\"0_4\":\"\",\"0_5\":\"\",\"1_0\":\"\",\"1_1\":\"\",\"1_2\":\"\",\"1_3\":\"\",\"1_4\":\"\",\"1_5\":\"\",\"2_0\":\"\",\"2_1\":\"\",\"2_2\":\"\",\"2_3\":\"\",\"2_4\":\"\",\"2_5\":\"\",\"3_0\":\"\",\"3_1\":\"\",\"3_2\":\"\",\"3_3\":\"\",\"3_4\":\"\",\"3_5\":\"\",\"4_0\":\"\",\"4_1\":\"\",\"4_2\":\"\",\"4_3\":\"\",\"4_4\":\"\",\"4_5\":\"\",\"5_0\":\"\",\"5_1\":\"\",\"5_2\":\"\",\"5_3\":\"\",\"5_4\":\"\",\"5_5\":\"\",\"C_1\":{\"className\":\"_dt-bold\"},\"D_1\":{\"className\":\"_dt-bold\"},\"E_1\":{\"className\":\"_dt-bold\"},\"F_1\":{\"className\":\"_dt-bold\"}},\"colTitles\":[\"A\",\"B\",\"C\",\"D\",\"E\",\"F\"],\"colWidths\":[138,100,116,100,100,100],\"data\":[[\"\",\"\",\"Total samples\",\"2\",\"Err\",\" 1.05\"],[\"Component\",\"Final conc\",\"1Rxn (uL)\",\"Total\",\"\",\"\"],[\"H2O\",\"\",\"3\",\"6.3\",\"\",\"\"],[\"rCutSmart Buffer\",\"\",\"1\",\"2.1\",\"\",\"\"],[\"SapI (10U/ul)\",\"10U\",\"1\",\"2.1\",\"\",\"\"],[\"Total\",\"\",\"5\",\"\",\"\",\"\"]],\"guid\":\"9806B2B9A1AC4D33AA184CFD15D85A52\",\"isJexcelDataFormat\":true,\"legend\":\"\",\"mergeCells\":{},\"printData\":[[\"\",\"\",\"Total samples\",\"2\",\"Err\",\" 1.05\"],[\"Component\",\"Final conc\",\"1Rxn (uL)\",\"Total\",\"\",\"\"],[\"H2O\",\"\",\"3\",\"6.3\",\"\",\"\"],[\"rCutSmart Buffer\",\"\",\"1\",\"2.1\",\"\",\"\"],[\"SapI (10U/ul)\",\"10U\",\"1\",\"2.1\",\"\",\"\"],[\"Total\",\"\",\"5\",\"\",\"\",\"\"]],\"rowHeights\":[23,23,23,23,23,23]}}}}",
  "steps": [
    "If the wild-type insert is obtained from PCR amplification, ensure the PCR product is cleaned. A B C 1 Component Final conc. 1Rxn (uL) 2 H 2 O Up to 25 ul 3 T4 DNA ligase buffer 1X 2.5 4 T4 DNA ligase (2,000U/ul) 0.5 5 Plasmid (100ng/ul) 2.5 ng 2.5 6 SapI (10U/ul) 20U 2 7 Insert (ul) 1:2 mol ratio 1.09 8 Total 25 A negative control reaction with H 2 O instead of insert is recommended. Set the thermal cycler for the program below: A B C 1 Step Temperature Time (hh:mm:ss) 2 1 37°C 00:05:00 3 2 16°C 00:05:00 4 3 Go to step 1 for 10-15 total cycles 5 4 60°C 00:15:00 6 5 85°C 00:15:00 7 6 4°C hold SapI enzyme is less thermostable. Consider adding 1 µL of SapI enzyme after 02:00:00 .",
    "Made additional digestion mix. A B C D E F 1 Total samples # 2 Err 1.05 2 Component Final conc 1Rxn (uL) Total 3 H 2 O 3 6.3 4 rCutSmart Buffer 1 2.1 5 SapI (10U/ul) 10U 1 2.1 6 Total 5 Aliquot 5 µL of digestion mix to each of the golden gate reactions. Set the thermal cycler for the program below: A B C 1 Step Temperature Time (hh:mm:ss) 2 1 55°C At least 2 hours 3 2 80°C 00:15:00 4 3 Hold at 4C",
    "Purify each reaction with Zymo Clean &amp; Concentrator -5 kit.",
    "Add 1 µL - 2 µL of DNA from sample reaction and negative control to chemical competent E. coli cells by following NEB Stable competent cell transformation protocol. Quick transformation without an outgrowth period is adequate. It will reduce transformation efficiency. Consider to add Puc 19 and H 2 O as controls to the transformation process.",
    "Incubate overnight at 30 °C for 24:00:00 .",
    "Check negative control plate to ensure the background colony is less than 10% of the colony counts from the sample plate.",
    "Pick 2-3 colonies for an overnight growth in 3 mL of LB + amp (1:1000) per colony for mini prep.",
    "Sequence confirmation by nanopore sequencing."
  ],
